  ">

    <!-- CARD 1 -->
    <div style="
      border:1px solid #e5e5e5;
      border-radius:16px;
      padding:24px;
    ">
      <h3 style="font-size:20px; margin-bottom:10px;">
        Services aren't always immediately clear
      </h3>
      <p style="color:#555; line-height:1.6;">
Potential customers may visit a website, social media page, physical store etc. but still leave unsure about what is being offered. Clearer communication helps customers understand services more quickly and confidently. </p>
    </div>

    <!-- CARD 2 -->
    <div style="
      border:1px solid #e5e5e5;
      border-radius:16px;
      padding:24px;
    ">
      <h3 style="font-size:20px; margin-bottom:10px;">
        Business communication looks inconsistent
      </h3>
      <p style="color:#555; line-height:1.6;">
As businesses grow across different platforms and materials, service information is often presented in different ways. Consistent messaging creates a clearer and more professional customer experience.      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- CARD 3 -->
    <div style="
      border:1px solid #e5e5e5;
      border-radius:16px;
      padding:24px;
    ">
      <h3 style="font-size:20px; margin-bottom:10px;">
Clearer messaging helps attract better-fit inquiries      </h3>
      <p style="color:#555; line-height:1.6;">
When service information lacks clarity, businesses may receive inquiries from customers who aren't the right fit. Better communication helps set clearer expectations and improves the quality of customer inquiries.      </p>
    </div>

  </div>
